  "conclusion": "All three variants produced zero hallucinations, confirming FirmSignal's source filtering is robust regardless of evidence threshold. Unexpectedly, the strict variant outperformed baseline (93.6 vs 90.9 avg score) — requiring two independent sources forced higher-quality evidence selection and more precise flag descriptions. The aggressive variant underperformed (86.4) primarily due to degraded citation quality on Boeing (0.5 vs 1.0) where single-source unverified claims reduced the brief's factual density. Risk flag count was identical across all variants (5.0 avg) indicating Claude hits the configured maximum in all cases — the variants affect flag quality not quantity. Decision: keep baseline setting. Strict mode is marginally better on quality metrics but would miss genuine single-source risks in breaking news scenarios. The current one-credible-source threshold balances precision and recall correctly."
